---
import { Button } from "@/components/ui/button";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import { ArrowLeft, BookmarkPlus, Calendar, Clock, Share2, User } from "lucide-react";
import { Badge } from "@/components/ui/badge";
import { Card, CardContent } from "@/components/ui/card";
import { Separator } from "@/components/ui/separator";
import { ArrowRight } from "lucide-react";
import Layout from "@/layouts/Layout.astro";
export const getStaticPaths = (() => {
    const blogPost = {
  id: 1,
  title: "How to Choose the Right Graphics Card for Gaming in 2024",
  content: `
    <p>Choosing the right graphics card is one of the most important decisions when building or upgrading a gaming PC. With so many options available from NVIDIA and AMD, it can be overwhelming to determine which GPU will provide the best performance for your specific needs and budget.</p>
    
    <h2>Understanding Your Gaming Requirements</h2>
    <p>Before diving into specific graphics card recommendations, it's crucial to understand what you want to achieve with your gaming setup. Consider the following factors:</p>
    
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Resolution:</strong> Are you gaming at 1080p, 1440p, or 4K?</li>
      <li><strong>Frame Rate Goals:</strong> Do you want 60fps, 120fps, or higher?</li>
      <li><strong>Game Types:</strong> Are you playing competitive esports titles or demanding AAA games?</li>
      <li><strong>Budget:</strong> What's your maximum spending limit?</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Current Market Leaders</h2>
    <p>As of 2024, the graphics card market is dominated by two major players:</p>
    
    <h3>NVIDIA RTX 40 Series</h3>
    <p>NVIDIA's latest RTX 40 series offers exceptional performance with features like DLSS 3, ray tracing, and excellent power efficiency. Popular models include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>RTX 4090 - Ultimate 4K gaming performance</li>
      <li>RTX 4080 - High-end 4K and excellent 1440p performance</li>
      <li>RTX 4070 Ti - Great 1440p gaming with ray tracing</li>
      <li>RTX 4060 Ti - Solid 1080p and entry-level 1440p gaming</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>AMD Radeon RX 7000 Series</h3>
    <p>AMD's RDNA 3 architecture provides competitive performance with excellent value propositions:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>RX 7900 XTX - Flagship performance competing with RTX 4080</li>
      <li>RX 7800 XT - Strong 1440p performance at a competitive price</li>
      <li>RX 7600 - Budget-friendly 1080p gaming solution</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Performance Recommendations by Resolution</h2>
    
    <h3>1080p Gaming</h3>
    <p>For smooth 1080p gaming at high settings, consider these options:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Budget ($200-300):</strong> RTX 4060, RX 7600</li>
      <li><strong>Mid-range ($300-500):</strong> RTX 4060 Ti, RX 6700 XT</li>
      <li><strong>High-end ($500+):</strong> RTX 4070, RX 7800 XT</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>1440p Gaming</h3>
    <p>1440p gaming requires more powerful hardware for optimal performance:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Entry-level:</strong> RTX 4060 Ti, RX 7600 XT</li>
      <li><strong>Recommended:</strong> RTX 4070, RX 7800 XT</li>
      <li><strong>High-end:</strong> RTX 4070 Ti, RX 7900 XT</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>4K Gaming</h3>
    <p>4K gaming demands the most powerful graphics cards available:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Minimum:</strong> RTX 4070 Ti, RX 7900 XT</li>
      <li><strong>Recommended:</strong> RTX 4080, RX 7900 XTX</li>
      <li><strong>Ultimate:</strong> RTX 4090</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Additional Considerations</h2>
    
    <h3>VRAM Requirements</h3>
    <p>Video memory (VRAM) is becoming increasingly important as games become more demanding. Here are general recommendations:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>1080p:</strong> 8GB minimum, 12GB recommended</li>
      <li><strong>1440p:</strong> 12GB minimum, 16GB recommended</li>
      <li><strong>4K:</strong> 16GB minimum, 20GB+ preferred</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Power Supply Requirements</h3>
    <p>Ensure your power supply can handle your chosen graphics card:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>RTX 4060/RX 7600:</strong> 550W PSU</li>
      <li><strong>RTX 4070/RX 7800 XT:</strong> 650W PSU</li>
      <li><strong>RTX 4080/RX 7900 XTX:</strong> 750W PSU</li>
      <li><strong>RTX 4090:</strong> 850W+ PSU</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>Final Recommendations</h2>
    <p>Based on current market conditions and performance data, here are our top picks for different scenarios:</p>
    
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Best Overall Value:</strong> RTX 4070 - Excellent 1440p performance with great efficiency</li>
      <li><strong>Best Budget Option:</strong> RX 7600 - Solid 1080p gaming at an affordable price</li>
      <li><strong>Best High-End:</strong> RTX 4080 - Outstanding 4K performance with DLSS support</li>
      <li><strong>Best Flagship:</strong> RTX 4090 - Unmatched performance for enthusiasts</li>
    </ul>

    <p>Remember that graphics card prices fluctuate frequently, so it's worth monitoring deals and considering previous-generation cards that may offer better value. Always ensure your system's other components (CPU, RAM, PSU) can support your chosen graphics card for optimal performance.</p>
  `,
  author: "Michael Rodriguez",
  date: "2024-01-15",
  readTime: "8 min read",
  category: "Hardware Guide",
  image: "/product-1.png",
  tags: ["GPU", "Gaming", "Hardware", "RTX", "AMD"],
}
    return [
        {
            params: {id: 1},
            props: {blogPost}
        }
    ];
});
const {params, props} = Astro;
const blogPost = props?.blogPost || {};

const relatedPosts = [
  {
    id: 2,
    title: "Building Your First Custom PC: A Complete Beginner's Guide",
    image: "/product-1.png",
    category: "Build Guide",
  },
  {
    id: 3,
    title: "RAM Upgrade Guide: How Much Memory Do You Really Need?",
    image: "/product-1.png",
    category: "Hardware Guide",
  },
]
---
<Layout>
    <div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8">
        {/* Back Button */}
        <div class="mb-6">
          <Button variant="ghost" className="hover:bg-green-50">
            <a href="/blog" class="flex items-center">
              <ArrowLeft className="h-4 w-4 mr-2" />
              Back to Blog
            </a>
          </Button>
        </div>
    
        <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-4 gap-8">
          {/* Main Content */}
          <article class="lg:col-span-3">
            {/* Header */}
            <div class="mb-8">
              <Badge className="bg-green-100 text-green-800 mb-4">{blogPost.category}</Badge>
    
              <h1 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">{blogPost.title}</h1>
    
              <div class="flex items-center text-gray-600 mb-6">
                <User className="h-4 w-4 mr-2" />
                <span class="mr-4">{blogPost.author}</span>
                <Calendar className="h-4 w-4 mr-2" />
                <span class="mr-4">{new Date(blogPost.date).toLocaleDateString()}</span>
                <Clock className="h-4 w-4 mr-2" />
                <span>{blogPost.readTime}</span>
              </div>
    
              <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
                <Button variant="outline" size="sm">
                  <Share2 className="h-4 w-4 mr-2" />
                  Share
                </Button>
                <Button variant="outline" size="sm">
                  <BookmarkPlus className="h-4 w-4 mr-2" />
                  Save
                </Button>
              </div>
            </div>
    
            {/* Featured Image */}
            <div class="mb-8">
              <Image
                src={blogPost.image || "/placeholder.svg"}
                alt={blogPost.title}
                width={800}
                height={400}
                class="w-full h-64 md:h-96 object-cover rounded-lg"
              />
            </div>
    
            {/* Content */}
            <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none mb-8" set:html={blogPost.content} />
    
            {/* Tags */}
            <div class="mb-8">
              <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4">Tags</h3>
              <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-2">
                {blogPost.tags.map((tag, index) => (
                  <Badge key={index} variant="outline" className="hover:bg-green-50 cursor-pointer">
                    <a href={`/blog/tag/${tag.toLowerCase()}`}>{tag}</a>
                  </Badge>
                ))}
              </div>
            </div>
    
            <Separator className="my-8" />
    
            {/* Author Bio */}
            <Card className="mb-8">
              <CardContent className="p-6">
                <div class="flex items-start space-x-4">
                  <Image
                    src="/placeholder.svg?height=80&width=80"
                    alt={blogPost.author}
                    width={80}
                    height={80}
                    class="rounded-full"
                  />
                  <div>
                    <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">{blogPost.author}</h3>
                    <p class="text-gray-600 text-sm">
                      Lead Technician with over 12 years of experience in computer hardware and gaming systems.
                      Specializes in custom PC builds and performance optimization.
                    </p>
                  </div>
                </div>
              </CardContent>
            </Card>
          </article>
    
          {/* Sidebar */}
          <aside class="lg:col-span-1">
            <div class="space-y-6">
              {/* Related Posts */}
              <Card>
                <CardContent className="p-6">
                  <h3 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4">Related Articles</h3>
                  <div class="space-y-4">
                    {relatedPosts.map((post) => (
                      <a href={`/blog/${post.id}`} class="block group">
                        <div class="flex space-x-3">
                          <Image
                            src={post.image || "/placeholder.svg"}
                            alt={post.title}
                            width={80}
                            height={60}
                            class="rounded object-cover flex-shrink-0"
                          />
                          <div>
                            <Badge variant="outline" className="text-xs mb-1">
                              {post.category}
                            </Badge>
                            <h4 class="text-sm font-medium group-hover:text-green-600 transition-colors line-clamp-2">
                              {post.title}
                            </h4>
                          </div>
                        </div>
                      </a>
                    ))}
                  </div>
                </CardContent>
              </Card>
    
              {/* Newsletter */}
              <Card className="bg-green-50 border-green-200">
                <CardContent className="p-6 text-center">
                  <h3 class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Stay Updated</h3>
                  <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mb-4">Get the latest tech tips delivered to your inbox</p>
                  <Button className="w-full bg-green-600 hover:bg-green-700">Subscribe</Button>
                </CardContent>
              </Card>
            </div>
          </aside>
        </div>
    
        {/* Navigation */}
        <div class="flex justify-between items-center mt-12 pt-8 border-t">
          <Button variant="outline" className="hover:bg-green-50 bg-transparent">
            <ArrowLeft className="h-4 w-4 mr-2" />
            Previous Article
          </Button>
          <Button variant="outline" className="hover:bg-green-50 bg-transparent">
            Next Article
            <ArrowRight className="h-4 w-4 ml-2" />
          </Button>
        </div>
      </div>
</Layout>